<br>
Haste: Probably your most urgent upgrade.  The FBSS is a good recommendation.  If you want a Free option obtainable with a group at your level, go for the Grimling Skullcracker belt.  With the grimlings in the owbear cave, I was able to do the camp at around 35 with a similar level Shammy.  You can manipulate the war with a full group of 30's. Did it again last night for some youngsters in my guild on FV - Ended up with 6 belts in 3 hours (no caps, which is what we were after).  It's 11% haste with some decent stats, and it's free.  You'll want better though, and soon.  But I wouldn't worry about anything until you got some kind of haste.<br>
<br>
Helm: Upgrade to a Skull Shaped Barbute.  They should be fairly inexpensive on most servers (except FV - bah).<br>
<br>
Shoulder: If you can find a Tattered Mantle for cheap, pick it up.  It'll last you a good while. <br>
<br>
Legs: I prefer Crusty Legs over crafted - I think the added hps from STA are well worth the trade.  You may want to check that out.<br>
<br>
Ranged: You should probably look at saving up for a Goranga Idol.  You'll lose a few hps, but it will give you AC.  <br>
<br>
Hands:  May want to check out Gauntlets of the Black.  Dropped in the Ry'Gorr Fort, you may be able to get a group together to go after these at your level.  Otherwise, you could likely find them pretty cheap too.  <br>
<br>
Not sure how you feel about looting no-drop stuff from other people's kills, but if you happen to find someone killing dwarves in Icewell, the Royal Velium Frosted armor is no-drop and is very nice at your level.  My guild did Sentries and a few Sentinals when we were around 40, but it was difficult.  The boots and gloves drop fairly often from the easier Sentries, so if you find someone in there, they may let you loot some.  <br>
